  "prompt": "I'm in love with my FWB, should I stop having sex with him cause every time we have sex I get more attached to him?",
  "response": "It's completely understandable to develop deeper feelings in a Friends with Benefits (FWB) relationship. These arrangements can sometimes blur the lines between casual and emotional connections. Here are some steps and considerations to help you navigate your feelings:\n\n1. **Self-Reflection**:\n   - **Assess Your Feelings**: Take some time to understand the depth of your emotions. Are you experiencing temporary feelings, or do you envision a long-term relationship with your FWB?\n   - **Understand Your Needs**: Determine what you truly want from the relationship. Are you seeking commitment, or do you prefer to keep things casual?\n\n2. **Open Communication**:\n   - **Talk to Your FWB**: Share your feelings honestly and openly. Expressing your emotions can help both of you understand where you stand and what each party wants.\n   - **Set Clear Boundaries**: If you decide to continue the arrangement, establishing clear boundaries can help manage expectations and reduce the chances of further emotional attachment.\n\n3. **Evaluate the Relationship Dynamics**:\n   - **Compatibility**: Consider whether both of you are on the same page regarding the relationship's nature and future.\n   - **Impact on Friendship**: Think about how continuing or ending the sexual aspect might affect your existing friendship.\n\n4. **Consider Taking a Break**:\n   - **Distance for Clarity**: Sometimes, taking a step back can provide the space needed to evaluate your feelings and decide what's best for you.\n   - **Focus on Personal Well-being**: Use this time to engage in activities that make you happy and help you gain perspective.\n\n5. **Seek Support**:\n   - **Talk to Friends or a Counselor**: Sharing your feelings with trusted individuals or a professional can offer additional insights and support.\n\n6. **Evaluate Long-Term Goals**:\n   - **Future Expectations**: Reflect on where you see yourself in the future and whether the current arrangement aligns with those aspirations.\n\nUltimately, the decision to continue or end the sexual aspect of your relationship depends on what feels right for you. Prioritizing your emotional well-being is essential. Whether you choose to maintain the FWB arrangement with clarified boundaries or decide to step back to protect your feelings, ensure that your choice aligns with your personal needs and happiness.",
